 
 
This is documentation to explain creating a pub or an inn, using the pub
inheritable.
 
Always:
 
#include <mudlib.h>
inherit NEWPUB;
 
Do not inherit ROOM.  
 
There are a few functions which you have to define:
                          
set_type(string sArg);
  sArg = the type of store this is.  This is written to player, for example:
        "You cannot rob the " + type + ".\n"
  set_type("inn");
 
set_save_file(string sArg);
  sArg = filename of the save file for your pub/inn.  (Used with restore and save
        object.)
  set_storeroom("/players/myname/save_file");
 
set_bartender(string sArg, string sFilename);
  sArg = the name of the bartender, sFilename is the filename of it (with path.)
  set_bartender("bartender","players/myname/bartender_guy");
 
set_guard(string sArg);
  sArg = filename of the guard for that pub, that's called if the pub/inn
        is robbed.
  set_guard("/players/myname/guard");
 
add_item(string sArg, string sFilename, int iLimit);
  This is just like make_object, however, it accepts no 3rd argument for the
    number of that object.  It will make these drinks available, and they can 
    be bought buy the 1st arguement that you pass.  If you pass integer limit,
    then only that number will be sold, per reset.
  add_drink("beer","players/myname/neato_beer",10);
 
add_food(string sArg, int iLimit, int iCost, int iStrength);
  This is similar to add_item.  sArg is the name of the food.  iLimit is the 
    maximum number to be sold.  iCost is how puch to pay for it.  iStrength is 
    how many hit_points to heal them, and how satiated they get.
  add_food("bread",5,25,4); /* 5 breads, cost 25, heals 4 */
 
add_drink(string sArg, int iLimit, int iCost, int iStrength);
  This is similar to add_food.  All of the arguements are the same.  If you 
    want the drink to be unlimied, pass 0 for iLimit.
  add_drink("beer",0,2,2); /* unlimited beers, cost 2, heal 2 */
 
set_menu_color(string sArg);
  str = the color string, that you want the shop menu to display in.
        If you are unfamiliar with color strings, wizhelp 1.7 (ansi).
  set_menu_color("|RKB"); /* Red on Black, Bold */
 
Note:  At then end of your reset function, add the line restore();
       Change your if(iArg) return, to this:
         if(iArg) {
           restock();
           return;
         }
 
There are a few functions already in the init of NEWPUB:
  Buy/Order, Rob, and Read.  Read is setup, as you add items, or food to your
    pub or inn, the menu us modified.  Do *not* add_read or menu or sign.
    You do not need to add_action these.
  There is an 'exit_hook' function, please dir_hook the exits out of your pub
    and make them call exit_hook();  If this is a room with no alcohol served,
    then you do not have to do this.
 
The drinks for your pub, *must* return true for id("alcohol");  IE, set_alt_name
or set_alias to alcohol.
 
